---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Random Walks — Math Explorations | Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Interactive visualization of random walks showing the square root law and endpoint distribution patterns."
>
  <section class="demo-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Random Walks</h1>

      <div class="explanation">
        <p>Here's the experiment: stand in the middle of a field. Each step, flip a coin to pick a direction — north, south, east, or west — and walk one step. Do this 500 times. Where do you end up?</p>
        <p>I expected the answer to be "pretty far away." It's not. The average distance only grows with √n, not n. So 500 random steps only takes you about as far as 22 deliberate steps. I ran this simulation over and over because I didn't believe the numbers at first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-container">
        <div class="canvas-grid">
          <div class="canvas-section">
            <h2>Single Random Walk</h2>
            <canvas id="walkCanvas"></canvas>
            <div class="controls">
              <div class="control-group">
                <label for="stepsSlider">
                  Steps: <span id="stepsValue">500</span>
                </label>
                <input type="range" id="stepsSlider" min="100" max="5000" step="100" value="500">
              </div>

              <div class="control-group">
                <label for="speedSlider">Speed:</label>
                <select id="speedSlider">
                  <option value="10">Slow</option>
                  <option value="5" selected>Medium</option>
                  <option value="1">Fast</option>
                </select>
              </div>

              <div class="button-group">
                <button id="newWalkBtn">New Walk</button>
                <button id="pauseBtn">Pause</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="canvas-section">
            <h2>Endpoint Distribution</h2>
            <canvas id="distCanvas"></canvas>
            <div class="controls">
              <div class="control-group">
                <label for="numWalks">Number of Walks:</label>
                <select id="numWalks">
                  <option value="100">100</option>
                  <option value="500">500</option>
                  <option value="1000" selected>1000</option>
                  <option value="5000">5000</option>
                </select>
              </div>

              <div class="control-group">
                <label for="distSteps">Steps per Walk:</label>
                <select id="distSteps">
                  <option value="100">100</option>
                  <option value="500" selected>500</option>
                  <option value="1000">1000</option>
                </select>
              </div>

              <button id="runSimBtn">Run Simulation</button>

              <div class="stats">
                <p><strong>Average distance:</strong> <span id="avgDist">—</span></p>
                <p><strong>Expected (√n):</strong> <span id="expectedDist">—</span></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-matters">
        <h2>What Surprised Me</h2>
        <p>Run the endpoint simulation with 1000 walks. The dots form a circle. Every time. Pure randomness — each walk going in completely random directions — and they cluster in a perfect ring pattern. That broke my brain for a while.</p>
        <p>The √n thing also connects to stuff I didn't expect. It's why a drop of ink takes forever to spread through water (diffusion), and apparently it's related to why stock market diversification works. Doubling your random steps only gets you ~41% farther (√2 ≈ 1.41). Randomness is way more structured than I thought.</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="demo-nav">
        <a href="/math-explorations/primes">← Prime Spirals</a>
        <a href="/math-explorations/fourier">Next: Fourier Series →</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .demo-page {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .explanation {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #27AE60;
  }

  .demo-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .canvas-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .canvas-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .canvas-section {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  canvas {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .controls {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .control-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  #stepsValue {
    color: #27AE60;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--mid-gray);
    outline: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #27AE60;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #27AE60;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
  }

  select {
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .button-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  button {
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  .stats {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-left: 4px solid #27AE60;
  }

  .stats p {
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .stats span {
    color: #27AE60;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .why-matters {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--blue);
  }

  .demo-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .demo-nav a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    canvas {
      height: 300px;
    }

    .demo-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const walkCanvas = document.getElementById('walkCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const distCanvas = document.getElementById('distCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const stepsSlider = document.getElementById('stepsSlider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const stepsValue = document.getElementById('stepsValue') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const speedSlider = document.getElementById('speedSlider') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const newWalkBtn = document.getElementById('newWalkBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const pauseBtn = document.getElementById('pauseBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const numWalks = document.getElementById('numWalks') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const distSteps = document.getElementById('distSteps') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const runSimBtn = document.getElementById('runSimBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const avgDist = document.getElementById('avgDist') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const expectedDist = document.getElementById('expectedDist') as HTMLSpanElement;

  let walkAnimationFrame: number | null = null;
  let isPaused = false;

  function setupCanvas(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement) {
    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    canvas.width = rect.width * dpr;
    canvas.height = rect.height * dpr;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
    return { ctx, width: rect.width, height: rect.height };
  }

  function drawSingleWalk() {
    const steps = parseInt(stepsSlider.value);
    stepsValue.textContent = steps.toString();

    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas(walkCanvas);

    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    // Draw center
    ctx.fillStyle = '#E67E22';
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(width / 2, height / 2, 5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.fill();

    let x = width / 2;
    let y = height / 2;
    const scale = Math.min(width, height) / (2 * Math.sqrt(steps));
    let currentStep = 0;
    const frameDelay = parseInt(speedSlider.value);
    let frameCount = 0;

    function animate() {
      if (isPaused) {
        walkAnimationFrame = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
        return;
      }

      frameCount++;
      if (frameCount < frameDelay) {
        walkAnimationFrame = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
        return;
      }
      frameCount = 0;

      if (currentStep >= steps) return;

      const direction = Math.floor(Math.random() * 4);
      const dx = [1, 0, -1, 0][direction];
      const dy = [0, 1, 0, -1][direction];

      const newX = x + dx * scale;
      const newY = y + dy * scale;

      // Color gradient based on progress
      const hue = (currentStep / steps) * 360;
      ctx.strokeStyle = `hsl(${hue}, 70%, 50%)`;
      ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(x, y);
      ctx.lineTo(newX, newY);
      ctx.stroke();

      x = newX;
      y = newY;
      currentStep++;

      if (currentStep < steps) {
        walkAnimationFrame = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
      } else {
        // Draw endpoint
        ctx.fillStyle = '#3498DB';
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(x, y, 5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fill();
      }
    }

    animate();
  }

  function runDistributionSimulation() {
    const walks = parseInt(numWalks.value);
    const steps = parseInt(distSteps.value);

    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas(distCanvas);

    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    // Draw center
    ctx.fillStyle = '#E67E22';
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(width / 2, height / 2, 5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.fill();

    const endpoints: { x: number; y: number; dist: number }[] = [];
    const scale = Math.min(width, height) / (2 * Math.sqrt(steps) * 1.5);

    // Run walks
    for (let w = 0; w < walks; w++) {
      let x = 0;
      let y = 0;

      for (let s = 0; s < steps; s++) {
        const direction = Math.floor(Math.random() * 4);
        x += [1, 0, -1, 0][direction];
        y += [0, 1, 0, -1][direction];
      }

      const dist = Math.sqrt(x * x + y * y);
      endpoints.push({ x, y, dist });
    }

    // Calculate statistics
    const totalDist = endpoints.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.dist, 0);
    const avgDistance = totalDist / walks;
    const expected = Math.sqrt(steps);

    avgDist.textContent = avgDistance.toFixed(2);
    expectedDist.textContent = expected.toFixed(2);

    // Find max distance for color scaling
    const maxDist = Math.max(...endpoints.map(p => p.dist));

    // Draw endpoints
    endpoints.forEach(({ x, y, dist }) => {
      const px = width / 2 + x * scale;
      const py = height / 2 + y * scale;

      // Color by distance
      const ratio = dist / maxDist;
      const hue = 200 - ratio * 200; // Blue to orange
      ctx.fillStyle = `hsla(${hue}, 70%, 50%, 0.5)`;

      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(px, py, 3, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();
    });
  }

  stepsSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
    stepsValue.textContent = stepsSlider.value;
  });

  newWalkBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (walkAnimationFrame) {
      cancelAnimationFrame(walkAnimationFrame);
    }
    isPaused = false;
    pauseBtn.textContent = 'Pause';
    drawSingleWalk();
  });

  pauseBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    isPaused = !isPaused;
    pauseBtn.textContent = isPaused ? 'Resume' : 'Pause';
  });

  runSimBtn.addEventListener('click', runDistributionSimulation);

  window.addEventListener('resize', () => {
    if (!isPaused && walkAnimationFrame) {
      if (walkAnimationFrame) {
        cancelAnimationFrame(walkAnimationFrame);
      }
      drawSingleWalk();
    }
  });

  // Initial draws
  drawSingleWalk();
  runDistributionSimulation();
</script>
